---
<BaseLayout
  title="Koios · Science & evidence"
  description="A registered clinical trial, peer-reviewed publications, and hospitals across Belgium using the platform with real patients."
  page="science"
>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Science &amp; evidence</span>
      <h1 style="margin-top:18px">Credibility you can <em>cite</em>.</h1>
    </div>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:22px">A registered clinical trial, peer-reviewed publications, and hospitals across Belgium using the platform with real patients. The evidence behind the Q-index, in the open.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Q-INDEX EXPLAINED -->
<section style="padding-top:calc(20px*var(--density))">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Q-index</span>
      <h2>From raw sensor data to one clear measure.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The Q-index distils 40+ validated digital measures into a single, interpretable indicator of how quality of life is trending &mdash; designed to be read at a glance and shared with a care team.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qx-steps reveal">
      <div class="qs"><div class="n">01 &middot; CAPTURE</div><h3>Passive sensing</h3><p>Everyday phone and smartwatch sensors record movement, rest and heart-rate physiology continuously, with no tasks.</p></div>
      <div class="qs"><div class="n">02 &middot; MEASURE</div><h3>Validated digital measures</h3><p>Signal becomes 40+ measures of gait, tremor, sleep, activity and autonomic function, each validated against clinical references.</p></div>
      <div class="qs"><div class="n">03 &middot; COMPOSE</div><h3>The Q-index</h3><p>Measures are combined into a single composite that tracks quality-of-life trend over time, robust to day-to-day noise.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRIAL -->
<section style="background:var(--surface-2);border-top:1px solid var(--line);border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Clinical validation</span>
      <h2>A registered trial.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="trial-card reveal" style="margin-top:40px">
      <div class="hd">
        <span class="code">Q-index trial &middot; NCT06209502</span>
        <span class="st">Registered &amp; recruiting</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <div class="c"><div class="k">Condition</div><div class="v">Parkinson&rsquo;s disease</div></div>
        <div class="c"><div class="k">Design</div><div class="v">Prospective, real-world digital measures</div></div>
        <div class="c"><div class="k">Primary focus</div><div class="v">Quality-of-life trend (Q-index)</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="ft">An early signal from the programme: <b style="color:var(--ink)">57%</b> of participants reported an improvement in health-related quality of life, with <b style="color:var(--ink)">96%</b> of days captured passively.</div>
    </div>
    <p class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:18px">Trial identifier shown for reference. Koios Care is a wellness solution and is not a medical device; it does not diagnose or treat disease.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- RESEARCH IMPACT -->
<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Research impact</span>
      <h2>The science predates the company.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Koios grew out of a decade of published research on digital biomarkers. The founding team and advisors wrote the methods the platform builds on &mdash; measured here in citations, not claims.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="impact-strip reveal" style="margin-top:44px">
      <div class="ic"><span class="v"><span class="count" data-count="9700" data-suffix="+">9,700+</span></span><span class="k">combined citations across the team</span></div>
      <div class="ic"><span class="v"><span class="count" data-count={String(pubs.length)}>{pubs.length}</span></span><span class="k">selected publications &amp; proceedings</span></div>
      <div class="ic"><span class="v"><span class="count" data-count={String(areas.length || 5)}>{areas.length || 5}</span></span><span class="k">research areas, one platform</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="researchers">
      {RESEARCHERS.map((r, i) => (
        <article class="rsr card reveal" data-delay={String((i % 3) + 1)}>
          <div class="rsr-id">
            <div class={`rsr-ava ${r.group}`}><span>{r.initials}</span></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="rsr-name">{r.name}</h3>
              <div class="rsr-role">{r.role}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="rsr-stats">
            <div><span class="v count" data-count={String(r.citations)}>{fmt.format(r.citations)}</span><span class="k">Citations</span></div>
            <div><span class="v count" data-count={String(r.hIndex)}>{r.hIndex}</span><span class="k">h-index</span></div>
            <div><span class="v count" data-count={String(r.i10)}>{r.i10}</span><span class="k">i10-index</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="rsr-tags">
            {r.expertise.map((t) => <span class="tag">{t}</span>)}
          </div>
          <div class="rsr-paper">
            <span class="mono-label">Most cited</span>
            <p>{r.paper.title}</p>
            <span class="meta">{r.paper.year} &middot; {fmt.format(r.paper.citations)} citations</span>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:26px">Citation counts, h-index and i10-index from the team&rsquo;s public Google Scholar profiles &mdash; figures evolve as the literature does.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PUBLICATIONS -->
<section id="publications" style="background:var(--surface-2);border-top:1px solid var(--line)">
  <div class="wrap" style="max-width:920px">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Publications</span>
      <h2>Peer-reviewed &amp; presented.</h2>
      <p class="lead">From touchscreen typing to in-the-wild tremor detection &mdash; the team&rsquo;s work, by research area.</p>
    </div>

    {areas.length > 1 && (
      <div class="pub-filter reveal" role="group" aria-label="Filter publications by research area" style="margin-top:36px">
        <button class="active" data-area="all" aria-pressed="true">All <sup>{pubs.length}</sup></button>
        {areas.map((a) => (
          <button data-area={a} aria-pressed="false">{a} <sup>{areaCount(a)}</sup></button>
        ))}
      </div>
    )}

    <div class="pub-list reveal" style="margin-top:28px;border-top:1px solid var(--line)">
      {pubs.map((p) => (
        <div class="pub" data-area={p.area ?? ''}>
          <span class="yr">{p.year}</span>
          <div class="body">
            <h3>{p.url ? <a href={p.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{p.title}</a> : p.title}</h3>
            {p.authors && <div class="auth">{p.authors}</div>}
            <div class="meta-row">
              {p.source && <span class="src">{p.source}</span>}
              {p.area && <span class="area">{p.area}</span>}
              {p.citations && <span class="cit">{fmt.format(p.citations)} citations</span>}
            </div>
            {p.summary && <p>{p.summary}</p>}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PARTNERS -->
<section style="background:var(--surface-2);border-top:1px solid var(--line)">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Partners</span>
      <h2>Built with clinicians and research institutions.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="partners reveal" style="margin-top:36px">
      {partners.map(p => <span class="partner">{p.name}</span>)}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="dark cta">
  <div class="wrap reveal" style="text-align:center">
    <h2 style="margin:0 auto;max-width:18ch">Want the methods in detail?</h2>
    <p class="lead" style="margin:22px auto 0;text-align:center">We&rsquo;re glad to share validation data and discuss study collaborations.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;margin-top:32px">
      <a href="/about#contact" class="btn btn--on-dark">Contact the team <span class="arr">&rarr;</span></a>
      <a href="/pharma" class="btn btn--ghost on-dark">For research partners</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // ---- citation count-up ----
  // Markup ships with the final value, so content is correct without JS;
  // the animation only replaces it once the element scrolls into view.
  if (!matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches && 'IntersectionObserver' in window) {
    const nf = new Intl.NumberFormat('en-GB');
    const io = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        entries.forEach((e) => {
          if (!e.isIntersecting) return;
          io.unobserve(e.target);
          const el = e.target as HTMLElement;
          const target = parseInt(el.dataset.count || '0', 10);
          const suffix = el.dataset.suffix || '';
          const dur = 1300;
          const t0 = performance.now();
          const tick = (t: number) => {
            const p = Math.min((t - t0) / dur, 1);
            const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - p, 3); // settle gently
            el.textContent = nf.format(Math.round(target * eased)) + (p === 1 ? suffix : '');
            if (p < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
          };
          requestAnimationFrame(tick);
        });
      },
      { threshold: 0.6 }
    );
    document.querySelectorAll('.count').forEach((el) => io.observe(el));
  }

  // ---- publication area filter ----
  const filterBtns = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('.pub-filter button');
  const pubRows = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.pub-list .pub'));
  const animate = !matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
  filterBtns.forEach((btn) => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      filterBtns.forEach((b) => {
        b.classList.toggle('active', b === btn);
        b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(b === btn));
      });
      const area = btn.dataset.area;
      let i = 0;
      pubRows.forEach((row) => {
        const show = area === 'all' || row.dataset.area === area;
        row.classList.toggle('hide', !show);
        row.classList.remove('flash');
        if (show && animate) {
          row.style.setProperty('--i', String(i++));
          void row.offsetWidth; // restart the entrance animation
          row.classList.add('flash');
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  .trial-card{background:var(--surface-2);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);
    overflow:hidden;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
  .trial-card .hd{background:var(--primary);color:#fff;padding:16px 24px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;
    align-items:baseline;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px}
  .trial-card .hd .code{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.08em}
  .trial-card .hd .st{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;
    display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:7px;color:#fff}
  .trial-card .hd .st::before{content:"";width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--sage-bright)}
  .trial-card .bd{padding:24px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  .trial-card .bd .c{padding-right:24px;border-right:1px solid var(--line)}
  .trial-card .bd .c:last-child{border-right:none;padding-right:0}
  .trial-card .bd .k{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-dim)}
  .trial-card .bd .v{font-size:16px;color:var(--ink);margin-top:8px;font-weight:500}
  .trial-card .ft{padding:20px 24px;font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.6}
  @media(max-width:640px){.trial-card .bd{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:18px}.trial-card .bd .c{border-right:none;padding-right:0}}

  /* ---- research impact ---- */
  .impact-strip{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);border:1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius:var(--radius);overflow:hidden;background:var(--surface-2)}
  .impact-strip .ic{padding:30px 28px;border-right:1px solid var(--line)}
  .impact-strip .ic:last-child{border-right:none}
  .impact-strip .v{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(34px,3.6vw,46px);line-height:1;
    color:var(--accent);letter-spacing:-.02em;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums;display:block}
  .impact-strip .k{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--ink-mid);margin-top:12px;line-height:1.5;display:block}
  @media(max-width:760px){
    .impact-strip{grid-template-columns:1fr}
    .impact-strip .ic{border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
    .impact-strip .ic:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  }

  .researchers{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:20px;margin-top:20px}
  .rsr{display:flex;flex-direction:column;padding:26px 24px}
  .rsr-id{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px}
  .rsr-ava{flex:none;width:52px;height:52px;border-radius:999px;display:flex;align-items:center;
    justify-content:center;background:var(--primary-faint);transition:transform .3s var(--ease)}
  .rsr-ava span{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:19px;color:var(--primary)}
  .rsr-ava.advisor{background:var(--secondary-faint)}
  .rsr-ava.advisor span{color:var(--secondary)}
